ce:section.ce:para:
The -SH functionalized CQDs with better water solubility and stability were synthesized hydrothermally using chlorophyll as carbon precursor and glutathione as a -SH surface functionalization unit (Fig. 1
                        ). The synthesized GSHCQD shows UV–vis absorption spectra at around 270 nm and 325 nm, which corresponds to the π → π* and n → π* transitions (Fig. 2
                        a). From Fig. 2b, it can be seen that by changing the excitation wavelength (λex) from 300 nm to 480 nm, the emission wavelength also varies from 400 nm to 540 nm with a maximum emission at 420 nm (ex = 340 nm). The comparative study of FTIR spectra of chlorophyll with GSHCQD illustrates the formation of GSHCQD (Fig. S1).
